---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import profile from '../assets/profile.jpg';
import { getPlaceholder } from '../lib/placeholder';

const profilePlaceholder = await getPlaceholder(profile);
---
<section class="about-intro px-[var(--pad-page)] max-w-[1280px] mx-auto mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 items-start
    md:grid-cols-[5fr_7fr] md:gap-10 md:mt-12
    lg:gap-16 lg:mt-16">
  <figure class="about-studio portrait-shadow relative m-0 w-full">
    <Image
      src={profile}
      alt="Khin Sandar Kyaw in her Yangon studio"
      loading="lazy"
      class="relative z-[1] w-full h-auto aspect-[4/5] object-cover bg-cover bg-center filter grayscale contrast-[1.05]"
      style={`background-image: url('${profilePlaceholder}')`}
    />
    <figcaption class="mt-3 text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.16em] text-muted">
      The studio, Yangon — 2025
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="about-bio flex flex-col gap-6 text-[16px] leading-[1.65] md:pt-2">
    <p>I started painting in 2019, and since then it has become a meaningful part of my life. I'm especially drawn to realistic, reference-based art — whether it's a quiet landscape or a portrait full of personality. I enjoy taking time to observe details, study light, and explore how colors interact to shape emotion and mood in a piece.</p>
    <p>I work with a mix of mediums, mainly acrylic on canvas, wall painting, and pencil sketch. Each one gives me a different way to express ideas: acrylic for its boldness, murals for their scale and impact, and pencil for its simplicity and precision. No matter the medium, I love the process of slowing down, observing, and translating what I see onto a surface.</p>
    <p>Nature, portrait studies, and observation drawing are the areas that inspire me the most. I enjoy experimenting with color and finding new ways to bring everyday scenes and faces to life.</p>
    <p>I've also had the opportunity to take part in "The Light," a group art exhibition featuring multiple artists. For this show, I created around 10 artworks — each one representing a step forward in my artistic journey.</p>
  </div>
</section>
